- **Overview**
  - Use shadcn/ui as the primary UI system for Next.js projects.
  - This project uses shadcn/ui for **ALL** UI elements.
  - Ensure consistent, accessible components across the app by **ALWAYS** using shadcn/ui components.

- **Initialization (Required)**
  - If shadcn/ui is not initialized in the project, use the following command:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

  - **Do not** use `create-next-app` for initialization.
  - Reference: [Next.js + shadcn Installation Guide](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/installation/next)

- **Adding Components (Required)**
  - If a particular component is not installed, use the following command:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

  - Replace `button` with any needed component name from the catalog.
  - **All available components:** [shadcn/ui Components Catalog](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components)
  - Reference: [shadcn/ui Installation Guide](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/installation/next)

- **Component Usage Policy (Required)**
  - **ALWAYS** use shadcn/ui components for **ALL** UI elements: **inputs, textarea, select, buttons, dialogs, cards, tables, forms**, etc.
  - **NEVER** create UI primitives from scratch - shadcn/ui has comprehensive coverage of UI components.
  - **Do not** hand-build any UI components unless there is a compelling, documented reason and the component doesn't exist in shadcn/ui.
  - **Always** import from `@/components/ui/*` as generated by the shadcn CLI.
  - Check the [Components Catalog](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components) first before creating any custom UI element.

- **Examples**

```tsx
// Import from generated shadcn/ui paths
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";
import { Textarea } from "@/components/ui/textarea";
import {
  Select,
  SelectTrigger,
  SelectValue,
  SelectContent,
  SelectItem,
} from "@/components/ui/select";

export function ExampleForm() {
  return (
    <div className="space-y-4">
      <Button>Click me</Button>
      <Input placeholder="Your name" />
      <Textarea placeholder="Tell us more" />
      <Select>
        <SelectTrigger>
          <SelectValue placeholder="Choose one" />
        </SelectTrigger>
        <SelectContent>
          <SelectItem value="a">A</SelectItem>
          <SelectItem value="b">B</SelectItem>
        </SelectContent>
      </Select>
    </div>
  );
}
```

- **DO / DON'T**
  - **DO** initialize/configure with `npx shadcn@latest init`.
  - **DO** add components with `npx shadcn@latest add <component>`.
  - **DO** import from `@/components/ui/...` and keep APIs consistent.
  - **DO** check the [Components Catalog](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components) before building anything custom.
  - **DON'T** scaffold with `create-next-app`.
  - **DON'T** hand-build any UI primitives - use shadcn/ui for ALL UI elements.
  - **DON'T** create custom buttons, inputs, selects, dialogs, or any other UI components that exist in shadcn/ui.

- **Maintenance**
  - Periodically review new shadcn/ui components and updates; prefer official components when they cover your use case.
  - If a custom primitive is introduced, document rationale and ensure feature parity (keyboard nav, ARIA, focus states, theming).

